# Project Architecture

Overview: five libraries with strict layering; three conceptual flows (type hierarchy, Interactionsâ†’Transactions, onchain eventsâ†’projections) drive where to add new types, operations, and projections. Use the file reference table below and the linked rule files for detail.

- **Library layout**: Five libraries â€” `onchain-lib`, `chainsync-lib`, `offchain-lib`, `webapi-lib`, `mcp-server-lib`.
  - **Cabal dependency flow**: `offchain-lib` depends on `chainsync-lib` and `onchain-lib`; `webapi-lib` has no project-lib deps; `mcp-server-lib` depends on `offchain-lib` and `webapi-lib` and is consumed only by the `mcp-server` executable. Executables depend on `offchain-lib` and `webapi-lib`; `chainsync-service` also depends on `chainsync-lib`; `mcp-server` depends on `mcp-server-lib`.
  - **Layering** (inner â†’ outer): **onchain-lib** + **chainsync-lib** (inner) â†’ **offchain-lib** (domain, tx building, storage) â†’ **webapi-lib** (HTTP, auth, CORS) / **mcp-server-lib** (MCP HTTP adapter, thin client over query-api + interaction-api). Dependencies may only point inward (e.g. offchain-lib â†’ chainsync-lib, offchain-lib â†’ onchain-lib, mcp-server-lib â†’ offchain-lib + webapi-lib). Do not add cross-library dependencies that invert or bypass this (e.g. no webapi-lib â†’ offchain-lib, no chainsync-lib â†’ offchain-lib, nothing â†’ mcp-server-lib outside the `mcp-server` executable).
- **On-chain purity**: `onchain-lib` must never import off-chain dependencies (no Aeson, Servant, Swagger, etc.). PlutusTx types and instances live in onchain-lib; JSON/Swagger/orphan instances in offchain-lib.

## Conceptual flows

Keep these in mind when adding features. Each has a single canonical rule file for full detail.

- **Type hierarchy**: Transfer types (API DTOs in `DomainTypes/Transfer/Types.hs`) rely on Domain types (`DomainTypes/Core/Types.hs`, `Core/Actions.hs`), which rely on onchain types; `TxBuilding/Conversions.hs` bridges onchain datums â†” domain. New API shapes in Transfer; new domain entities in Core; new onchain types in `Onchain/Protocol/Types.hs` and `Id.hs`.
- **Interactions â†’ Transactions**: Interactions (action + user addresses) become transactions via Operations: `interactionToTxSkeleton` â†’ Operations (Skeletons + Lookups) â†’ `GYTxSkeleton` â†’ `interactionToTxBody` â†’ transaction. Do not bypass this pipeline. Execution runs in `TxBuildingContext`: `interactionToTxBody` is run with `runReaderT ... txBuildingCtx` and `runTx`; CLI uses `runBJJActionWithPK`. Build-tx vs submit (unsigned CBOR vs add-witness-and-submit) and provider usage are per executable; see [executables.mdc](executables.mdc) Â§ Build-tx vs submit and provider. Pipeline details: [offchain-rules.mdc](offchain-rules.mdc) Â§ Pipeline.
- **Context**: Tx building uses `DeployedScriptsContext` (validator refs + oracle; `MonadReader` in Operations/Lookups/Interactions) and `TxBuildingContext` (deployed scripts + provider) for `runTx`, `interactionToTxBody`, and `runBJJActionWithPK`. Executables load and pass context; see [executables.mdc](executables.mdc).
- **Onchain events â†’ database projections**: Chain-sync consumes validator-output matches; each match becomes a projection row via `projectChainEvent` (Ingestion) and `putMatchAndProjections` (Storage). New projection type â†’ extend `ChainEventProjection`, `projectChainEvent`, Storage `put*`, and **`rollbackTo`**. Details: [storage-ingestion.mdc](../operations/storage-ingestion.mdc).
- **Executables**: `admin` (CLI), `interaction-api` (port 8082), `query-api` (port 8083), `chainsync-service` (port 8084; sources in `src/exe/chain-sync/`), `mcp-server` (port 8085). The interaction-api and query-api expose HTTP APIs and Swagger UI; they are the boundary for UIs and clients (e.g. wallet UIs, future frontends). `mcp-server` exposes the same surface over Model Context Protocol for AI clients by wrapping query-api + interaction-api via HTTP â€” no direct DB or chain access of its own. When adding features: new actions â†’ interaction API; new queries â†’ query API; new projections â†’ chain-sync + Storage/Ingestion; new MCP tools â†’ mcp-server-lib. Implementation patterns and startup flow: see [executables.mdc](executables.mdc).
- **File reference** â€” where to change what. Paths are under `src/lib/<lib>/` or `src/exe/<exe>/`; onchain = `onchain-lib`, tx/domain/storage = `offchain-lib`.

