### Query API layout (`src/exe/query-api/`)

When adding or changing read endpoints, start with routes and handlers; add or edit supporting modules only when the feature needs them.

- **`RestAPI.hs`** â€” Servant route types, server record, Swagger wiring.
- **`RestAPI/Common.hs`** â€” Holds only `withBackend` (bound to `QueryAppMonad`). See [executables.mdc](executables.mdc) Â§ *Query API specifics* for `withBackend` and live vs projected.
- **`Query/Projected.hs`** / **`Query/Live.hs`** â€” Projected (DB) vs live (chain) implementations.
- **`Query/Common.hs`** â€” Shared pagination and ordering helpers used by both backends.
- **Response DTOs** (`*Response`, `*PageResponse`, aggregate responses) live in `offchain-lib/DomainTypes/Transfer/QueryResponses.hs` â€” exposed by offchain-lib so other executables (e.g. the MCP server) can reuse them without duplication. Keep shapes not in `DomainTypes/Transfer/Types.hs` here, with `ToSchema`.
- **Filter record types** and their `*FromParams` builders live in `offchain-lib/DomainTypes/Transfer/Filters.hs`.
- **Sort / order enums** (`SortOrder`, `*OrderBy`, `ActivityEventType`) live in `offchain-lib/DomainTypes/Transfer/OrderBy.hs`.
- **Small focused helpers** â€” use for localized concerns scoped to query-api; keep cross-executable concerns in `offchain-lib/DomainTypes/Transfer/*`.
